<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Drug_addiction&amp;action=edit&amp;section=28" title="Edit section: Literature">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Literature</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Sainsbury, <i>Drug and the Drug Habit</i> (New York, 1909)</li>
<li>C. A. McBride, <i>Modern Treatment of Alcoholism and Drug Narcotism</i> (New York, 1910)</li>
<li>G. E. Pettey, <i>Narcotic Drug Diseases and Allied Ailments</i> (Philadelphia, 1913)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Fitz_Hugh_Ludlow" title="Fitz Hugh Ludlow">Fitz Hugh Ludlow</a> wrote <i>The Hasheesh Eater</i> (1857) and <i>The Opium Habit</i> (1868), designed as a warning.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Thomas_de_Quincey" title="Thomas de Quincey">Thomas de Quincey</a>, <i>Confessions of an English Opium Eater</i> (London, 1822)</li>
